{"id":1653932,"retrievedAt":"2026-03-19T11:55:07.542Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/rwfIlm3yZDWogcF9npfZUC4H5Ye.jpg","belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"","id":1653932,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["PL","SE","US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Discovering Edmund","overview":"When director Isabella Kolb learned that her great-great-uncle was imprisoned in Stutthof, the first German concentration camp established on Polish soil during the Second World War, she begins an investigation into his story and the camp's little-known history. Despite its significance, Stutthof remains one of the least documented sites of Nazi persecution, leaving families of its victims with lingering questions.  Through witness testimonies and archival traces, the film follows Kolb's search for Uncle Edmund and the lives of those who endured Stutthof, offering a quiet reflection on memory, loss, and the lasting echoes of trauma that continue to shape the generations that followed.","popularity":0.0071,"poster_path":"/pXhQo58cC21OUOnboYvercno5.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","name":"United States of America"}],"release_date":"2025-11-23","revenue":0,"runtime":49,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"English","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English"},{"english_name":"Polish","iso_639_1":"pl","name":"Polski"},{"english_name":"Swedish","iso_639_1":"sv","name":"svenska"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"Discovering the History of Stutthof Concentration Camp","title":"Discovering Edmund","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":2523017,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Manfred Goldberg","original_name":"Manfred Goldberg","popularity":0.0362,"profile_path":"/jCetuhRFg9Ew3EBpgnWJJPiP9vq.jpg","cast_id":4,"character":"","credit_id":"69baa6bf798a53ea652c9397","order":0},{"adult":false,"ge